## ⛔ GROUND TRUTH — read FIRST, every session, every agent

**[docs/PROJECT_FACTS.md](docs/PROJECT_FACTS.md) is Tier 0 memory.** It lists retired/renamed
components, hard constraints, and environment facts, and it **overrides any conflicting
assumption** in prompts, specs, or model training. If a task references anything marked
`RETIRED`/`superseded` there, STOP and flag it.

- Add or change a fact with **`/remember <fact>`** — it propagates to every future session and
  every subagent automatically (no more re-typing "X is retired" into each session).
- Memory model + supersession rules: `.claude/skills/core/shared-context-protocol.md`.
- **Every agent-spawn prompt MUST prepend the ground-truth injection line** (see the protocol
  skill, Layer 2). Orchestrators do this automatically.

