## Test Enforcement (CRITICAL — every agent must follow)

### TC-* Test Case ID System
Every spec defines explicit test case IDs (TC-* format). Every test file must annotate which TC-* IDs it covers. The phase gate blocks if any HIGH/MEDIUM TC-* ID is missing.

- **Specs generate TC-* IDs** using matrices from `test-case-generation.md`:
  - Unit: 10+ per spec (edge cases, error paths)
  - Integration: 10 per endpoint + 6 per entity (auth, validation, IDOR, shapes)
  - E2E: 5+ per workflow (happy path, validation, errors, permissions, persistence)
  - UI: 10+ per page + 8 per form (4-states, interactions, responsive, accessibility)
  - Acceptance: 5+ per persona-FR pair (positive, negative permission boundaries, cross-persona)

- **Test agents** extract their responsible TC-* IDs at Phase 0, annotate every test, and self-check before completing
- **spec_test_reconciler** blocks the gate if `implemented < specified` for HIGH+MEDIUM priority

### Per-Phase Test Tiers (ALL mandatory, ALL non-zero)
| Tier | Agent | Gate Check |
|------|-------|------------|
| Unit | unit_test_agent | report exists + total > 0 + 80% coverage |
| Integration | integration_test_agent | report exists + total > 0 |
| E2E (browser or CLI/pipeline) | ui_test_agent / e2e | report exists + total > 0 |
| Acceptance (persona-based) | acceptance_test_agent | report exists + total > 0 |

### Cross-Phase Enforcement
- Step 3a.5: re-run unit + integration + E2E for affected phases
- Gate: full regression (all tiers, all phases) before gate.passed
- `/accept`: local deploy + health gate + full regression + global acceptance + TC-* inventory reconciliation + pipeline completeness validation
- Local deploy: `/accept` Step 0a builds, migrates, starts, and health-checks the app before any acceptance testing. Unhealthy deploy caps release readiness at NOT READY.
- Pipeline completeness: holistic chain audit (requirements -> BRD -> specs -> code -> tests -> acceptance) with scored verdict. Completeness < 80% vetoes release readiness.
- Adaptive replanning: Wave 5 classifies failures and determines minimum re-test scope (see `adaptive-replan.md`)
- Change-impact regression: Wave 6 gate runs only tests affected by current phase's changes (see `change-impact-analysis.md`)
- Model routing: agents with `model: auto` select haiku/sonnet/opus based on complexity (see `model-routing.md`)

