## Memory Model (three tiers — see `.claude/skills/core/shared-context-protocol.md`)

| Tier | Where | Load policy | Add via |
|------|-------|-------------|---------|
| **0 — Facts** | [docs/PROJECT_FACTS.md](docs/PROJECT_FACTS.md) | ALWAYS (every session + subagent) | `/remember` |
| **1 — Lessons/Patterns** | `agent_state/lessons.md`, `agent_state/patterns.md` | On demand — query by category/tag (`memory-as-tools.md`) | auto after each gate |
| **2 — Codebase KB** | `agent_state/codebase/` | When relevant — load the focused doc | `/map` |

- Tier 0 facts are **bi-temporal**: a superseding fact closes the old one's validity window
  (deterministic `(subject, relation)` match — never semantic similarity). History is preserved.
- Never load a whole Tier 1/2 file for a narrow question — retrieve by tag. Run `/consolidate`
  periodically to dedup and keep memory lean.

